import { useState } from 'react'
import {
  Container,
  Nav,
  NavLogo,
  BodyContainer,
  Library,
  Song,
  SongInfo,
  ControlPanel,
  FontAwesome,
  SongName,
  AuthorName
} from './MusicPlayerFullElements.js'
import {
  faPause,
  faPlay,
  faTimes
} from '@fortawesome/free-solid-svg-icons'

const MusicPlayerFull = () => {
  const [libraryStatus, setLibraryStatus] = useState(true)
  return (
    <>
      <Container>
        <Nav>
          <NavLogo to='/'>Indielog</NavLogo>
          <FontAwesome size='2x' icon={faTimes} onClick={() => setLibraryStatus(!libraryStatus)}/>
        </Nav>
        <BodyContainer>
          <Library libraryStatus={libraryStatus}>
          </Library>
          <Song libraryStatus={libraryStatus}>
            <SongInfo>
              <SongName>SuckDIDI</SongName>
              <AuthorName>SUCKDIDILONG</AuthorName>
            </SongInfo>
            <ControlPanel>
            </ControlPanel>
          </Song>
        </BodyContainer>
      </Container>
    </>
  )
}

export default MusicPlayerFull
